12/04/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The state prosecution in Belgrade on Friday (April 10th) pressed charges against one person suspected of setting a fire at the US embassy in Belgrade during last year's February 21st riots after Kosovo's unilateral declaration of independence. The prosecution announced that Milan Ivanovic faces charges of posing a serious threat to public security and theft. If found guilty, Ivanovic could serve up to 12 years in prison. (B92, BTA - 10/04/09)
